# BSS export → React (no manual wiring in src/)

Cloudey frontend wiring must not diverge from Bootstrap Studio export.

## Only edit

1. **`bss-export/`** (BSS HTML output) — `data-cloudey`, `data-cloudey-type`, structure, classes
2. **`bss_exporter/templates/cloudey.config.json`** — mapping keys to hook `wires`
3. **`bss_exporter/templates/*.ts`** — hook implementations copied to `src/hooks/` on export

## Never edit for functionality

- `src/pages/**/*.tsx` — generated from BSS HTML; re-export to change
- `src/hooks/**`, `src/layout/**`, `src/context/**` after export — copied from templates; edit templates then re-export

Do not add `data-cloudey`, `onSubmit`, alert blocks, or modal wiring directly in `src/`. If BSS lacks an attribute, leave React unwired until BSS is fixed and export runs again.

## Fixes

- Missing attribute → add in BSS, ensure key exists in `cloudey.config.json`, re-export
- Wrong behavior → update `bss_exporter/templates/` hook or config, re-export
- Do not patch generated `LoginPage.tsx` (etc.) as a shortcut
